      "description": "Available for acquisition is a mechanically sorted 2004 BMW M3 (E46) featuring the high-revving S54 3.2L inline-six engine. This power unit utilizes six individual throttle bodies and a dual-VANOS variable valve timing system, which has been recently overhauled to ensure optimal volumetric efficiency. Power is routed through a 6-speed Getrag manual gearbox to a variable M-differential lock, providing exceptional traction and corner-exit stability. The chassis has been enhanced with a subframe reinforcement kit to mitigate floor fatigue, while the suspension retains its factory-tuned geometry for a balanced roll center. While the exterior displays minor stone chips from enthusiast use, the drivetrain is in excellent health, having undergone a recent valve clearance adjustment and rod bearing service. A robust, performance-oriented example for the discerning driver.",
